## ✅ Subtask 2.1 Completed

I've successfully implemented the search filter helper function. Here's a summary:

### What was done:

**Created `matchesSearchFilter(todo)` helper function** in `newTab.js` (lines 1311-1321):

```javascript
// Helper function to check if a todo matches the current search filter
function matchesSearchFilter(todo) {
  // If no search filter, all todos match
  if (!currentSearchFilter) return true;

  const searchLower = currentSearchFilter.toLowerCase();
  const titleMatch = (todo.title || "").toLowerCase().includes(searchLower);
  const descMatch = (todo.description || "").toLowerCase().includes(searchLower);

  return titleMatch || descMatch;
}
```

### Key features:
- ✅ Returns `true` when search filter is empty (shows all todos)
- ✅ Case-insensitive matching using `toLowerCase()`
- ✅ Checks both `todo.title` and `todo.description`
- ✅ Handles null/undefined fields gracefully with `|| ""` fallback
- ✅ Clean, readable code following existing patterns

### Commits:
1. `44bdb0e` - Add matchesSearchFilter helper function
2. `16773d8` - Update subtask 2.1 status to completed

### Next subtasks to implement:
- **2.2**: Update `renderBoard()` filter logic to use `matchesSearchFilter()`
- **2.3**: Update `refreshTodoList()` filter logic to use `matchesSearchFilter()`

