## ✅ Subtask 2.3 Completed

I've successfully implemented the search filter in `refreshTodoList()` for list view consistency.

### Changes Made

**File:** `newTab.js` (lines 3950-3959)

Modified the todo filtering logic to apply `matchesSearchFilter()` in all three project filter branches:

```javascript
items.todos.forEach((todo) => {
  // Only render todos that match the current project filter and search filter
  if (
    (currentProjectId === "all" && matchesSearchFilter(todo)) ||
    (currentProjectId === "none" && !todo.projectId && matchesSearchFilter(todo)) ||
    (todo.projectId === currentProjectId && matchesSearchFilter(todo))
  ) {
    renderTodo(todo, false);
  }
});
```

This mirrors the exact same filtering pattern used in `renderBoard()` (lines 1853-1857), ensuring consistency between:
- **Kanban board view** (`renderBoard()`) 
- **List view** (`refreshTodoList()`)

### Commits
- `2aa4c6f` - Add search filter to refreshTodoList()
- `3570506` - Update implementation plan - mark subtask 2.3 complete

### Build Progress
- **Phase 2 Complete**: 3/3 subtasks ✅
- **Overall**: 6/9 subtasks (67%)
- **Next Phase**: Polish and Testing (3 remaining subtasks)

